16/04/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- On Tuesday (15 April), government officials met with OSCE experts to discuss media legislation.
The talks were part of the process aiming to harmonise the Croatian media law with standards and practices in other European countries.
Also Tuesday, the daughter of former President Franjo Tudjman went on trial, charged with abuse of power.
Nevenka Tudjman, 50, is accused of using her family's position to secure profitable jobs for her business associates.
(HINA, HRT, AFP - 15/04/03)
